            <div class="col-md-4"><div class="card card-quiet p-3 h-100"><h5>Docs & training</h5><p class="small text-muted mb-0">Step‑by‑step install guides.</p></div></div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
<section id="how" class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <h2 class="text-center fw-bold">How it works</h2>
        <p class="text-center text-muted">Modeled after <a href="https://www.nycmesh.net/" target="_blank">NYC Mesh</a> and other <a href="https://wiki.vonet.org/index.php?title=Community_Networks">Community Networks</a>. Decentralized and resilient. </p>
        <div class="row g-3 mt-1">
            <div class="col-md-4"><div class="card card-quiet p-3 h-100"><span class="badge bg-dark">1</span><h5 class="mt-2">Survey & line of sight</h5><p class="small text-muted mb-0">We map rooftops and high points.</p></div></div>
            <div class="col-md-4"><div class="card card-quiet p-3 h-100"><span class="badge bg-dark">2</span><h5 class="mt-2">Install a node</h5><p class="small text-muted mb-0">Mount antenna, run cable, power gear.</p></div></div>
            <div class="col-md-4"><div class="card card-quiet p-3 h-100"><span class="badge bg-dark">3</span><h5 class="mt-2">Link neighbors</h5><p class="small text-muted mb-0">Each node extends coverage.</p></div></div>
            <div class="col-md-4"><div class="card card-quiet p-3 h-100"><span class="badge bg-dark">4</span><h5 class="mt-2">Add uplinks</h5><p class="small text-muted mb-0">Bridge to the wider internet.</p></div></div>
            <div class="col-md-4"><div class="card card-quiet p-3 h-100"><span class="badge bg-dark">5</span><h5 class="mt-2">Keep it open</h5><p class="small text-muted mb-0">Network Commons License guides use.</p></div></div>
        </div>

        <div class="row g-3 mt-3">
            <div class="col-lg-6">
                <div class="card card-quiet p-3 h-100">
                    <h5>Architecture</h5>
                    <ul class="small text-muted mb-0">
                        <li>Core services in a local data center.</li>
                        <li>Wireless relays on rooftops and towers.</li>
                        <li>Wired backhaul where it helps stability.</li>
                        <li>Planned regional Internet Exchange Point.</li>
                        <li>Managed address space and routing.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-6">
                <div class="card card-quiet p-3 h-100">
                    <h5>Gear (examples)</h5>
                    <div class="table-responsive small">
                        <table class="table table-sm align-middle mb-0">
                            <thead><tr><th>Use</th><th>Model</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr><td>Client</td><td>Ubiquiti LiteBeam AC</td><td>Low cost, solid for short links.</td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Relay</td><td>MikroTik LHG 5</td><td>Good gain. Light on rooftops.</td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Hub</td><td>Ubiquiti Rocket + Sector</td><td>Serve many clients per block.</td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Core</td><td>x86 Router + Switch</td><td>VLANs, BGP, monitoring.</td></tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

