<!-- FAQ (kept short; full FAQ lives on Wiki) -->
<section id="faq" class="section bg-white border-top">
    <div class="container">
        <h2 class="text-center fw-bold">FAQ</h2>
        <p class="text-center text-muted small">See the full <a href="https://wiki.vonet.org/index.php?title=FAQ" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">FAQ on the Wiki</a>.</p>
        <div class="accordion mt-3" id="faqAcc">
            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="h1"><button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#c1">Is there a monthly fee?</button></h2>
                <div id="c1" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAcc"><div class="accordion-body small text-muted">No. Access is donation‑based. Most connect at no cost for equipment. </div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="h2"><button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#c2">Is this an ISP like COX or Lumen?</button></h2>
                <div id="c2" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAcc"><div class="accordion-body small text-muted">VONet is a community-owned network, not a commercial ISP. We operate under the Network Commons License, building and running our own infrastructure at the same level as major providers like COX or Lumen. We connect to the internet through the same type of direct uplinks they use, which makes us just as reliable. We are not a simple relay or hotspot, and we do not sell or resell internet. Every connection is part of a resilient, community-built system designed to stay open, neutral, and independent.</div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="h3"><button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#c3">How fast is it?</button></h2>
                <div id="c3" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAcc"><div class="accordion-body small text-muted">We target connection speeds of 20 Mbps. But on good links, speeds can reach up to 100 Mbps. Actual speed depends on how far the signal travels and link quality. Each extra node adds more paths, making the network steadier and often faster for everyone.</div></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

